6 charecters<br>
Rillen-a wizard born in paineel.  Brother to Gerald, he was weeded out of the population of Paineel at a young age for his ineptitude at any of the darker crafts.  As a wizard he was not entirely shuned by his people, but when he chose the agnostic path, they were less than kind toward him.  His friends include hokulani(hoku), Brenan(Bren), Paren(sometimes Par), Ulla, and Forna.  The friends met all met in the warrens.  Rillen, Ulla, Bren, and Hoku had been friends before, but the six became close soon after fighting together.  This is where I would like to start the RP, but it could be anywhere.<br>
Ulla-Rillen's closest friend.  There is a connection between the two beyond friendship, but not quite in the erotic area(yet)  She is a mage of Erudin and sister to Hokulani.<br>
Hoku-Her and Paren start off quite apprehensive towards eachother due to some lued comments made on his part.  Their relationship grows into something beautiful and twisted all in one, although love doesn't blossom until quite some time later.  Both her part and Paren's would be fun to play in my opinion.<br>
Brenan-a cleric of rodcet knife.  He is an erudite of erudin of course.  He met Rillen by saving his life with a heal spell and the aid of his club against a herd of skeletons.  They later met the sisters having a spat over a gem dropped by a kobold.  He is quite alloof, but loves all his friends and will do anything within his power to aid them.<br>
Paren-The drinking halfelvish bard of Qeynos.  He often sings the wrong song for the occasion and rarely thinks about what he says until after hes said it.  He is the most outgoing and friendliest of the six, and this leads him often into trouble.<br>
Forna-A human monk with a wicked kick.  When shes night bonking heads, shes eating like a cow.  She often tries to bring Brenan out because she sees something in him that screams greatness.  Her antics, much as Parens are foolish and comical all at once.  Even in battle she keeps her spirits up and her stomach full.  Well, here you go.  Someone please join, I'm rather bored.  Oh, and the spot of Rillen is NOT reserved by me.  In fact, I'd much rather play another, and if all six spots are taken, you can just join as a random charecter, but it would be better if the original six are taken first.<br>
There also is the charecter of Gerald.  His isn't really one of the friends, but I guess someone could play him.  He is Rillen's brother and a rapidly rising necromancer.  At times, he comes to the aid of the friends, but he can also be jack ass as he laughs at their plight and may refuse help if he isn't in the right mood.   <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/02 4:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I'll take Paren haha sounds like fun</span><hr size=1> Humming a stupid tune that would not leave his head, Paren sat in darkness while he waited for his friends to show up. He scratched his foot as a bug crawled across it. &quot;Blasted bug!&quot; Lifting it off the ground he threw it into the small stream that trickled past him. Continuing to hum the same rediculous song he thought his eyes caught some movement. Sighing out of impatiances, he stood up and stretched. &quot;Where is everyone this morning?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Beetle man, Beetle man, doing the things that a beetle can. Walking with one foot and eatting with two, Beetle man, he's gotta shell that looks real new, what would happen if I smashed him with my shoe. Then he'd be beetle goo, bettle man.&quot; Smiling at the small fire beetle run across the ground he stapped it with his long sword. The bug cried out and died. Laughing at his song and his good fortune to have found a stupid bug, Paren looked around again for his friends. &quot;They should have been here ages ago! What could be holding those slackers up!&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rillen@fantasystoriesforum>Rillen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Weaver of Flames</span><br>  Posts: 270<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/02 6:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Me be Bren</span><hr size=1> OOC (I've decided to be Brenan.)<br>
