n>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/02 6:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Adventures of Rillen and the Gang</span><hr size=1> As yet another claw dug into his back Paren screamed as his last hold on his father's sword was ripped away. Looking up at the kobold with blood running from his eyes he sang the first song he could think of. The kobold smiled but was soon torn apart. Magic glittered in his eyes. Paren fell on the ground face up. he saw the claws flying and the other fighter still teariing into them. If only his father had taught him to fight with a sword better, or his mother taught him a stronger song. Grunting as another kobold stepped on him considering him no longer a danger Paren looked up at the sky. Leaves, there were so many of them in the dark forest. One he remembered trying to count them, he would just have to again. Feeling his chest torn and his ribs break as a kobold gave it's dying swipe at him he wondered. Where are my friends, I hope to the gods that I had not lost their friendship as well. Swearing he looked back to the leaves. He begged the good spirits to take care of his friends and ward them from this mess. He had not died with the honor he had intetended. As his blood spilled on the ground Paren figured out something, death is death no matter how glorious, death can only end one way. Smiling a wicked smile Paren tried as best he could to lean his head up to see another kobold explode from his directed song. &quot;My young brother! Go I'll guard you're back as well as I can. Run and find my friends, take my sword and make sure they understand that danger is coming! Now Go!&quot; starting his last chords, the one he had learned from his mother before he left home, Denon's Disruptive Discord. Screaming it out as loud as he could and enforicing it and braiding the power with the chords of dissonance, all the Kobolds turned their bleeded ears to his full attention. &quot;To Innorruk with you creatures!&quot; Paren wished it was enough to help the furry creature to get away. The power in the song took all the rest that Paren had and he could not stop the power from hurting himself, and as the blood ran from his own ears, Paren could no longer hear and the tone of his songs only lightened and grew stronger.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bonaki>Bonaki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/02 6:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Last stand</span><hr size=1> Hearing a horrible song reverberate through the trees, the stranger smiled as he reconized the song. &quot;Someone must be dying.&quot; he commented to his traveling compainion. The young girl nodded. &quot;Should we help?&quot; Shaking his head the man in black looked down at the girl. &quot;My dear cleric, that voice is beyond your help. And my sword can only kill. You have yet to study for a position of that power to help where all seems lost.&quot; The girl nodded with a tear in her eye. &quot;I became a cleric to help people and I'll be damned if I don't at least try.&quot; With a pout the girl started off. &quot;Amy, get your stubborn butt back here right now.&quot; Looking over her shoulder the girl gave a sigh. &quot;Yavi, I do not care what you say your sword can do, I've seen you with it and though I am appaled to be around your type of man, one who would only kill for his fair share, you are my guardian, but not my mentor and my mentor would be very displeased if I did not help. As my guardian you must guard me that is your job, you will help.&quot; Smiling the man pulled his sword. &quot;Let us go then, and kill us some kobolds.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=12.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=12.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=12.topic&start=61&stop=78>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=12.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=20><img src=http://Auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.emailToFriend?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.threadControl?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffan